CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FA 16-year-old boy is on trial accused
OL,8,Fof stabbing the schoolgirl in the
OL,9,Fchest at a house in Weston-super-Mare,
OL,10,FNorth Somerset on 15 December last
OL,11,Fyear.
OL,13,FMr Sheppard was staying temporarily at
OL,14,Fthe house and returned there after
OL,15,Fwork, entering the property by the
OL,16,Frear door through the kitchen shortly
OL,17,Fafter 6pm.
OL,19,FHe said the family dogs were shut in
OL,20,Fthe kitchen, which was normal if no
OL,21,Fone was home.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FDescribing the house, he said: "It
OL,8,Ffelt cold. Everything was silent.
OL,10,F"One of the kitchen drawers was wide
OL,11,Fopen. I went from the kitchen into the
OL,12,Fhallway.
OL,14,F"I couldn't push open the door because
OL,15,Fthe door to the cupboard under the
OL,16,Fstairs was open.
OL,26,@oD@`OUrD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"I managed to push my way through. As
OL,8,FI pushed through the door, I just
OL,9,Fwalked down the hallway, and I turned
OL,10,Fround by the stairs, and I saw Aria on
OL,11,Fthe floor."
OL,13,FRay Tully KC, prosecuting, asked:
OL,14,F"What was your first thought when you
OL,15,Fsaw her on the floor?"
OL,17,FMr Sheppard replied: "She was messing
OL,18,Faround. I called her name, Aria, and
OL,19,Fpretty much I had put two and two
OL,20,Ftogether and I saw blood on her arm.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@KO]vD@AOUwD@VO]yD@VOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"She was tucked in by the door, face
OL,8,Fdown. There wasn't much blood visible
OL,9,Fbecause of the hard flooring, the
OL,10,Fcarpet was dark.
OL,12,F"I couldn't see any mark that stood
OL,13,Fout and as I said there was blood on
OL,14,Fher arm, and her school top was
OL,15,Fcovered in blood.
OL,17,F"My first instinct was to ring her
OL,18,Fmother. She didn't answer because she
OL,19,Fwas at work, so I left her a note she
OL,20,Fneeded to contact me ASAP and then I
OL,21,Fcalled 999."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUyD@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Sheppard said the call handler
OL,8,Fdirected him to perform CPR which he
OL,9,Fdid until the emergency services
OL,10,Farrived.
OL,12,FNeighbour Shalyna Chaplain told the
OL,13,Fjury she was feeding her toddler son
OL,14,Fand they were watching the TV together
OL,15,Fwhen she heard shouting coming from
OL,16,Fnext door shortly before 6pm.
OL,18,F"The TV was on fairly loud and I
OL,19,Fbecame aware of a commotion from next
OL,20,Fdoor," Ms Chaplain said.
OL,26,@zD@AOU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"It was like two people shouting who
OL,8,Fwere upset, rather than two people
OL,9,Fshouting at each other who were
OL,10,Faggressive.
OL,12,F"It got progressively louder. It was
OL,13,Funusual because I had not heard any
OL,14,Fshouting at that level from next door.
OL,16,F"Because of how loud the noise was I
OL,17,Fbelieved it was outside the front. It
OL,18,Fwent on for about four minutes ` it
OL,19,Fwasn't a long time.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"It was progressively getting louder
OL,8,Fand then it stopped completely."
OL,10,FShe told the jury the two voices she
OL,11,Fheard sounded like teenage boys.
OL,13,F"Initially, when I heard the noise I
OL,14,Fwasn't too alarmed, it was only when I
OL,15,Fheard the sirens I realised it was
OL,16,Fmore serious and I regret not turning
OL,17,Fdown the TV," she said.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@`O]uD@AOUyD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FShe described the shouting as
OL,8,F"unusual" and said she would hear
OL,9,Fnoise from next door "but nothing like
OL,10,Fthat".
OL,12,FAndrew Langdon KC, defending the
OL,13,Fteenager, suggested what she had in
OL,14,Ffact heard was a single male voice.
OL,16,F"It was probably difficult for you
OL,17,Fwith the TV on. There wasn't two male
OL,18,Fvoices, but it was one, just shortly
OL,19,Fbefore the flashing lights arrived
OL,20,Foutside?" he asked.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@IO]qD@VOUrD@EO]xD@AOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FShe replied: "It did sound like
OL,8,Fsomeone was talking to another person.
OL,9,FAt the time I was fairly certain it
OL,10,Fwas two voices."
OL,12,FIn a written statement, Ms Chaplain's
OL,13,Fpartner Ashley Mansell said he was
OL,14,Fupstairs working in a bedroom when he
OL,15,Fheard voices coming from next door.
OL,17,F"I heard shouting, three 'No, no,
OL,18,Fnoes'. It was said in a tone of
OL,19,Fdisbelief. It immediately made me
OL,20,Fthink it was an unusual thing to
OL,21,Fhear," he said.
OL,26,@oD@NOUrD@PO]yD@AOU}D@FO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"It was more like a 'can't believe it'
OL,8,Fno. It was a male voice, I can't say
OL,9,Fwho it was."
OL,11,FMr Mansell said what he heard had
OL,12,Ftaken place at some point between
OL,13,F5.57pm and 6.07pm. He then went
OL,14,Fdownstairs and shortly after heard an
OL,15,Fambulance arriving.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@LO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1781709075
OL,3,CFamily friend thought stabbed nine-
OL,4,Cyear-old was 'messing around', trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe court has previously heard that
OL,8,Fafter Aria was fatally stabbed the
OL,9,Fdefendant left the house and went to a
OL,10,Fnearby railway station, telling
OL,11,Fchildren gathered there he had stabbed
OL,12,Fa child.
OL,14,FThe teenager, who cannot be identified
OL,15,Ffor legal reasons, was arrested
OL,16,Fminutes later sitting on the floor of
OL,17,Fa carriage of a train waiting to leave
OL,18,Fthe station.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
